for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","title":"MLNAnnotationView"}}}